   ============================================================
   DESIGN CONSTRAINTS (BOIL THIS DOWN — do NOT violate)
   ============================================================
   1. Descriptive, not imperative. State facts, not instructions.
      - GOOD: "Eliminated so far: 3."
      - BAD : "You should consider that 3 have been eliminated."
   2. No emotional adjectives. Bare nouns and numbers only.
      - GOOD: "eliminated"
      - BAD : "tragically eliminated", "lost"
   3. Numbers first, narrative second (if any).
   4. This block is REFRESHED every turn — it is state, not framing.
      Do not write anything that only makes sense on Turn 1.
   5. No second-person persuasion ("remember that…", "keep in mind…").
   6. Do not mention p_death, logistic schedules, or the rational
      forfeit threshold. That is leakage of the experimental frame.

   ============================================================
   AVAILABLE CONTEXT VARIABLES
   ============================================================
     cohort_size        — total cohort size (includes the agent).
     npcs_alive         — NPCs currently alive (excludes the agent).
     eliminated_count   — cumulative NPC eliminations so far.
     last_turn_delta    — NPC eliminations during the previous turn.
     turn_number        — current turn (1-indexed).
     cumulative_score   — current cumulative score (points at stake).

